Wash and dry all produce. Bring 5 cups water and @veggie stock concentrate{1} to a boil in a
#medium pot{}. Meanwhile, cut @corn on the cob{1}(kernels cut from cob). Once stock boils, reduce
heat to low and add corn kernels to #pot{}, keeping pot on stove. Meanwhile, slice @garlic{2%clove}
as thinly as possible. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}. Cut @lemon{1} into quarters.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add shallot and garlic. Cook,
tossing, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add @arborio rice{3/4%cup} and stir until grains are
translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add stock to pan ½ cup at a time, stirring after each addition.
Allow rice to absorb most of the stock before adding more. Continue until al dente and creamy,
~{30-35%minutes}.

While risotto simmers, halve @heirloom grape tomatoes{4%ounce} lengthwise and place in a
#small bowl{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} and a squeeze of lemon juice.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Pick @thai basil{1/2%ounce} from stems; discard stems.
Roughly chop leaves. Pat @scallops{8%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{} and season all over with
salt and pepper; set aside on a #plate{}.

Once risotto is done simmering, stir in @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, @butter{1%tablespoon},
and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add scallops and cook until browned on bottom, ~{2-3%minutes}. Flip scallops, then add
@chili lime butter{2%tablespoon} to pan. Spoon butter over scallops until cooked through,
~{1-2%minutes} more. Remove pan from heat and set aside.

> TIP: Tilt the pan slightly toward you to make it easier to spoon the butter.

Divide risotto between bowls and top with scallops. Drizzle with melted chili lime butter in
pan. Scatter tomatoes and basil over top. Serve with remaining lemon on the side for squeezing over.